00:12:36.590 --> 00:12:41.490
don't want to do a bunch of extra effort to go

00:12:41.620 --> 00:12:47.040
from the canonical format that we're going to use for all

00:12:47.040 --> 00:12:49.480
of this to actually streaming it to users, right?

00:12:49.620 --> 00:12:50.900
We shouldn't need to re-encode or anything like

00:12:50.900 --> 00:12:51.220
that.

00:12:51.220 --> 00:12:57.340
